overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, which included database and API endpoints, against
  a detailed specification. The assistant performed a thorough analysis,
  identifying both well-implemented features and significant gaps, such as the
  absence of a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, and outbound links in
  the report. Following this review, the assistant began implementing the first
  high-priority item: integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness
  interference. This involved updating data types, validation rules, and the
  user interface to include a slider for severity input and a critical safety
  warning for high severity scores, ensuring the application better meets the
  specified acceptance criteria."
